===Marriage and issue===
White married on January 7, 1903 in [[Washington, D.C.]]<ref name = "Callahan1"/><ref name = "WVDCH9">{{Citation | url = http://www.wvculture.org/vrr/va_mcdetail.aspx?Id=10997127 | title = Marriage Record Detail: Robert White | work = West Virginia Vital Research Records | publisher = West Virginia Division of Culture and History | accessdate = November 17, 2013}}</ref> to Mabel Glasscock Fitch,<ref name = "Callahan1"/><ref name = "WVUAA1"/><ref name = "WVDCH9"/> the only child and daughter of E. H. Fitch and his wife Laura Glasscock Fitch.<ref name = "Callahan1"/> Fitch was a native of [[Vanceburg, Kentucky|Vanceburg]], [[Kentucky]]<ref name = "Callahan1"/> and she attended [[Marshall University|Marshall College]] while her family resided in [[Huntington, West Virginia|Huntington]].<ref name = "Callahan1"/> Fitch completed her education in Washington, D.C.<ref name = "Callahan1"/> White and his wife Mabel had five children:<ref name = "Callahan1"/>

*John Baker White<ref name = "Callahan1"/><ref name = "WVDCH2">{{Citation | url = http://www.wvculture.org/vrr/va_bcdetail.aspx?Id=2581898 | title = Birth Record Detail: John Baker White | work = West Virginia Vital Research Records | publisher = West Virginia Division of Culture and History | accessdate = November 17, 2013}}</ref> (born February 11, 1904)<ref name = "WVDCH2"/>
*Mabel Glasgow White Cornwell<ref name = "Callahan1"/><ref name = "WVDCH3">{{Citation | url = http://www.wvculture.org/vrr/va_bcdetail.aspx?Id=2582113 | title = Birth Record Detail: Mabel Glasgow White | work = West Virginia Vital Research Records | publisher = West Virginia Division of Culture and History | accessdate = November 17, 2013}}</ref> (born February 18, 1906),<ref name = "WVDCH3"/> married James Leighton Cornwell on August 25 1926 in Hampshire County<ref name = "WVDCH8">{{Citation | url = http://www.wvculture.org/vrr/va_mcdetail.aspx?Id=10996159 | title = Marriage Record Detail: Mabel Glasgow White | work = West Virginia Vital Research Records | publisher = West Virginia Division of Culture and History | accessdate = November 17, 2013}}</ref>
*Elizabeth Steele White<ref name = "Callahan1"/><ref name = "WVDCH4">{{Citation | url = http://www.wvculture.org/vrr/va_bcdetail.aspx?Id=2582161 | title = Birth Record Detail: Elizabeth Steele White | work = West Virginia Vital Research Records | publisher = West Virginia Division of Culture and History | accessdate = November 17, 2013}}</ref> (born April 23, 1908)<ref name = "WVDCH4"/>
*Roberta Huston White McFarland<ref name = "Callahan1"/><ref name = "WVDCH5">{{Citation | url = http://www.wvculture.org/vrr/va_bcdetail.aspx?Id=2582070 | title = Birth Record Detail: Roberta Huston White | work = West Virginia Vital Research Records | publisher = West Virginia Division of Culture and History | accessdate = November 17, 2013}}</ref><ref name = "WVDCH10">{{Citation | url = http://www.wvculture.org/vrr/va_mcdetail.aspx?Id=11989828 | title = Marriage Record Detail: Roberta Huston White | work = West Virginia Vital Research Records | publisher = West Virginia Division of Culture and History | accessdate = November 17, 2013}}</ref> (born June 18, 1912),<ref name = "WVDCH5"/> married William Frank McFarland on June 13, 1936 in [[New Cumberland, West Virginia|New Cumberland]]<ref name = "WVDCH10"/>
*Robert White, Jr.<ref name = "Callahan1"/>

White's wife Mabel was an active member of the [[Presbyterianism|Presbyterian]] church<ref name = "Callahan1"/> and died on July 5, 1915<ref name = "Callahan1"/> and was [[burial|interred]] at [[Indian Mound Cemetery]] in Romney.<ref name = "HH1">{{Citation | url = http://www.historichampshire.org/cems/IndMnd-T-Z.htm | title = Indian Mound Cemetery: Hampshire County's Most Historic Cemetery - List of Interments | work = HistoricHampshire.org | publisher = HistoricHampshire.org, Charles C. Hall | accessdate = November 17, 2013}}</ref>

== Later life and death ==
White never remarried following his wife's death in 1915.<ref name = "WVDCH6"/> After several months of illness,<ref name = "NYT1"/> White died at his residence in Romney on August 15, 1935 at the age of 59<ref name = "WVDCH6"/><ref name = "NYT1"/><ref name = "WVDCH7">{{Citation | url = http://www.wvculture.org/vrr/va_dcdetail.aspx?Id=4969159 | title = Death Record Detail: Robert White | work = West Virginia Vital Research Records | publisher = West Virginia Division of Culture and History | accessdate = November 17, 2013}}</ref> due to [[arteriosclerosis]] and [[myocarditis]].<ref name = "WVDCH6"/><ref name = "WVDCH7"/> White was interred with Masonic rites on Saturday afternoon, August 17, 1935<ref name = "WVDCH6"/><ref name = "NYT1"/><ref name = "WVDCH7"/> at Indian Mound Cemetery in Romney.<ref name = "WVDCH6"/><ref name = "HH1"/><ref name = "WVDCH7"/>

